column5: After yesterdays miss, today I was out for redemption. I won't go into too much detail as I'm tired but here are some pics. Missed two, brought two to shore and properly landed one 24 inch beauty.
See- when ya have FUN ya CATCH!  Good job!  Michael
Way to go RC. I knew you could do it   never a doubt  Slayer
Thanks Mike! This morning I'm sore from all the hiking... That's fun too. Haha.  Pikeslayer- are you gonna rehire me now or what?
congrats does this mean i won't be getting your fishing gear
Nice! Glad to see you finaly had a good day! Keep it up!
Haha that's exactly what it means.
Nice going chad.  I'm not sure I'll ever travel to a place I find more beautiful than superior's north shore.
Nice fish! I'm glad you enjoyed yourself on Superior!  TDunn
Nice one Chad    Great work dude
Man that's some fishy looking water.  Colour me jealous!
let me know if you manage to make it to that river i mentioned.  i might head up there in a few days myself.

Ends up I hiked myself out on a few other rivers so I didn't make it to the spot you recommended. I caught this one at a very non-descript spot.... suprised me even. I'm back in North Bay now... next time I'm in your area I'll give you a msg.  Air Canada lost my tackle bag... imagine how happy I am now.
